  "text": "following from (II.2). The ranges of P (k) form a vector sub-bundle E of the trivial bundle T d × C N that will be called the valence subbundle. We shall denote by n its rank, i.e. the dimension of the ranges of projectors P (k). Necessarily, n is even due to the time-reversal symmetry (II.3). In d = 2, 3, the vector bundle E is trivializable. This follows from the vanishing of its first Chern number(s), another consequence of (II.3) [CITATION_1] . The trivializability of E means that there exists a smooth family (e i (k))",
